script = ExtResource("3_ex2wr")
category = 3
text = "In the mysterious land of Befre, within unexplored forests, lay creatures unexplained by modern science and research. Creatures that do not even follow logic of modern animals. The \"Mahrul Demons\", as called by many of the ethnic groups, spark an interesting connection with the icy hollows. Despite sightings growing more and more popular, sightings of these beings has existed since documented arrival 1000 years ago.

The term Mahrul Demons has been popularised to describe them, but the scientific term for these was made \"The Organts\". Organts remain an itch in Befre's history, they only get weirder as time goes on. They tie into multiple categories: Mimics, Frozoids, Spectres and Incrids. Mimics are the most tame of the bunch, they look like regular domestic animals that live wild round Befre. Yet they are accompanied by a magical feel, one that cannot be described to those who have not experienced the aura of the Icy Hollows. Mimics can be of vast influence by this \"Frostly Aura\" but they typically are not much more aggressive than regular varients of that animal. It is believed that the highly believed-in \"Wolf God\" Garmr is some varient of a Mimic, a very large wolf infused with the aura. Frozoids is where it gets interesting. They are creatures with no true anatomy, merely monsters made of ice and snow that are not even connected just floating pieces that make shape of humanoids and animals. A common Frozoid type are golems that can be seen as anything up to 4m in height, and all frozoids are known to take aggression to humans, but strangely ignore animals.

Spectres are deemed some of the scarier Organts. They are commonly told in ghost stories because of their similar experience. These creepy hunters are quiet and stalk their prey. Their appearance is consisten to shadowy creatures connected with the same aura as the Frozoids, except its more snow darkness. As they are extremely rare, there are only tales of them and not even a single picture. Areas that have tales of Spectres also report an amount of disappearances over a years period. Lastly there exist Incrids, who are simply unbelievable creatures. They are amalgamations on different animals in certain areas that were almost stitched together by this magical energy. Incrids are the rarest of them all but whenever spotted they are extremely aggressive towards human life. They are also believed to have fantastic senses as they are only noticed once the human is already being hunted. It seems as their physical abilities are their limit but as they seem to have extreme variety and versatility so it is not definite.

Having noticed the increased sightings of the Organts, Jonish and the government are even more intrigued to research them and the Icy Hollows than before. Despite the rural population adapting to living near these dangers, it still is important to research them to be able to properly protect the country's people. Although, there was still the issue of the restriction of foreign scientist that is and will definitely slow down this process."
id = 17
name = "Beferian Creatures"
gdscript = ExtResource("1_d4qwe")
